The paper presents a method for Bayesian inference of deep generative models using stochastic gradient MCMC. This involves using neural networks to estimate the intractable expectation over hidden variables. The paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
